357 static bool HasNative(AMDGPULibFunc::EFuncId id) { 0
358 switch(id) { 0
359 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_DIVIDE: 0
360 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_COS: ----
361 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_EXP: ----
362 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_EXP2: ----
363 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_EXP10: ----
364 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_LOG: ----
365 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_LOG2: ----
366 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_LOG10: ----
367 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_POWR: ----
368 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_RECIP: ----
369 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_RSQRT: ----
370 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_SIN: ----
371 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_SINCOS: ----
372 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_SQRT: ----
373 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_TAN: ----
374 return true; 0
375 default:; 0
376 } ----
377 return false; 0
378 } ----

434 FunctionCallee AMDGPULibCalls::getFunction(Module *M, const FuncInfo &fInfo) { 0
435 // If we are doing PreLinkOpt, the function is external. So it is safe to ----
436 // use getOrInsertFunction() at this stage. ----
437 ----
438 return EnablePreLink ? AMDGPULibFunc::getOrInsertFunction(M, fInfo) 0
439 : AMDGPULibFunc::getFunction(M, fInfo); 0
440 } ----

447 bool AMDGPULibCalls::isUnsafeMath(const CallInst *CI) const { 0
448 if (auto Op = dyn_cast(CI)) 0
449 if (Op->isFast()) 0
450 return true; 0
451 const Function *F = CI->getParent()->getParent(); 0
452 Attribute Attr = F->getFnAttribute("unsafe-fp-math"); 0
453 return Attr.getValueAsBool(); 0
454 } ----
455 ----
456 bool AMDGPULibCalls::useNativeFunc(const StringRef F) const { 0
457 return AllNative || llvm::is_contained(UseNative, F); 0
458 } ----
459 ----
460 void AMDGPULibCalls::initNativeFuncs() { 0
461 AllNative = useNativeFunc("all") || 0
462 (UseNative.getNumOccurrences() && UseNative.size() == 1 && 0
463 UseNative.begin()->empty()); 0
464 } 0
465 ----
466 bool AMDGPULibCalls::sincosUseNative(CallInst *aCI, const FuncInfo &FInfo) { 0
467 bool native_sin = useNativeFunc("sin"); 0
468 bool native_cos = useNativeFunc("cos"); 0
469 ----
470 if (native_sin && native_cos) { 0
471 Module *M = aCI->getModule(); 0
472 Value *opr0 = aCI->getArgOperand(0); 0
473 ----
474 AMDGPULibFunc nf; 0
475 nf.getLeads()[0].ArgType = FInfo.getLeads()[0].ArgType; 0
476 nf.getLeads()[0].VectorSize = FInfo.getLeads()[0].VectorSize; 0
477 ----
478 nf.setPrefix(AMDGPULibFunc::NATIVE); 0
479 nf.setId(AMDGPULibFunc::EI_SIN); 0
480 FunctionCallee sinExpr = getFunction(M, nf); 0
481 ----
482 nf.setPrefix(AMDGPULibFunc::NATIVE); 0
483 nf.setId(AMDGPULibFunc::EI_COS); 0
484 FunctionCallee cosExpr = getFunction(M, nf); 0
485 if (sinExpr && cosExpr) { 0
486 Value *sinval = CallInst::Create(sinExpr, opr0, "splitsin", aCI); 0
487 Value *cosval = CallInst::Create(cosExpr, opr0, "splitcos", aCI); 0
488 new StoreInst(cosval, aCI->getArgOperand(1), aCI); 0
489 ----
490 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("usenative", dbgs() << " replace " << *aCI 0
491 << " with native version of sin/cos"); ----
492 ----
493 replaceCall(sinval); 0
494 return true; 0
495 } ----
496 } 0
497 return false; 0
498 } ----
499 ----
500 bool AMDGPULibCalls::useNative(CallInst *aCI) { 0
501 CI = aCI; 0
502 Function *Callee = aCI->getCalledFunction(); 0
503 ----
504 FuncInfo FInfo; 0
505 if (!parseFunctionName(Callee->getName(), FInfo) || !FInfo.isMangled() || 0
506 FInfo.getPrefix() != AMDGPULibFunc::NOPFX || 0
507 getArgType(FInfo) == AMDGPULibFunc::F64 || !HasNative(FInfo.getId()) || 0
508 !(AllNative || useNativeFunc(FInfo.getName()))) { 0
509 return false; 0
510 } ----
511 ----
512 if (FInfo.getId() == AMDGPULibFunc::EI_SINCOS) 0
513 return sincosUseNative(aCI, FInfo); 0
514 ----
515 FInfo.setPrefix(AMDGPULibFunc::NATIVE); 0
516 FunctionCallee F = getFunction(aCI->getModule(), FInfo); 0
517 if (!F) 0
518 return false; 0
519 ----
520 aCI->setCalledFunction(F); 0
521 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("usenative", dbgs() << " replace " << *aCI 0
522 << " with native version"); ----
523 return true; 0
524 } 0
525 ----
526 // Clang emits call of __read_pipe_2 or __read_pipe_4 for OpenCL read_pipe ----
527 // builtin, with appended type size and alignment arguments, where 2 or 4 ----
528 // indicates the original number of arguments. The library has optimized version ----
529 // of __read_pipe_2/__read_pipe_4 when the type size and alignment has the same ----
530 // power of 2 value. This function transforms __read_pipe_2 to __read_pipe_2_N ----
531 // for such cases where N is the size in bytes of the type (N = 1, 2, 4, 8, ..., ----
532 // 128). The same for __read_pipe_4, write_pipe_2, and write_pipe_4. ----
533 bool AMDGPULibCalls::fold_read_write_pipe(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B, 0
534 const FuncInfo &FInfo) { ----
535 auto *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction(); 0
536 if (!Callee->isDeclaration()) 0
537 return false; 0
538 ----
539 assert(Callee->hasName() && "Invalid read_pipe/write_pipe function"); 0
540 auto *M = Callee->getParent(); 0
541 auto &Ctx = M->getContext(); 0
542 std::string Name = std::string(Callee->getName()); 0
543 auto NumArg = CI->arg_size(); 0
544 if (NumArg != 4 && NumArg != 6) 0
545 return false; 0
546 auto *PacketSize = CI->getArgOperand(NumArg - 2); 0
547 auto *PacketAlign = CI->getArgOperand(NumArg - 1); 0
548 if (!isa(PacketSize) || !isa(PacketAlign)) 0
549 return false; 0
550 unsigned Size = cast(PacketSize)->getZExtValue(); 0
551 Align Alignment = cast(PacketAlign)->getAlignValue(); 0
552 if (Alignment != Size) 0
553 return false; 0
554 ----
555 Type *PtrElemTy; ----
556 if (Size <= 8) 0
557 PtrElemTy = Type::getIntNTy(Ctx, Size * 8); 0
558 else ----
559 PtrElemTy = FixedVectorType::get(Type::getInt64Ty(Ctx), Size / 8); 0
560 unsigned PtrArgLoc = CI->arg_size() - 3; 0
561 auto PtrArg = CI->getArgOperand(PtrArgLoc); 0
562 unsigned PtrArgAS = PtrArg->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace(); 0
563 auto *PtrTy = llvm::PointerType::get(PtrElemTy, PtrArgAS); 0
564 ----
565 SmallVector ArgTys; 0
566 for (unsigned I = 0; I != PtrArgLoc; ++I) 0
567 ArgTys.push_back(CI->getArgOperand(I)->getType()); 0
568 ArgTys.push_back(PtrTy); 0
569 ----
570 Name = Name + "_" + std::to_string(Size); 0
571 auto *FTy = FunctionType::get(Callee->getReturnType(), 0
572 ArrayRef(ArgTys), false); ----
573 AMDGPULibFunc NewLibFunc(Name, FTy); 0
574 FunctionCallee F = AMDGPULibFunc::getOrInsertFunction(M, NewLibFunc); 0
575 if (!F) 0
576 return false; 0
577 ----
578 auto *BCast = B.CreatePointerCast(PtrArg, PtrTy); 0
579 SmallVector Args; 0
580 for (unsigned I = 0; I != PtrArgLoc; ++I) 0
581 Args.push_back(CI->getArgOperand(I)); 0
582 Args.push_back(BCast); 0
583 ----
584 auto *NCI = B.CreateCall(F, Args); 0
585 NCI->setAttributes(CI->getAttributes()); 0
586 CI->replaceAllUsesWith(NCI); 0
587 CI->dropAllReferences(); 0
588 CI->eraseFromParent(); 0
589 ----
590 return true; 0
591 } 0
592 ----
593 // This function returns false if no change; return true otherwise. ----
594 bool AMDGPULibCalls::fold(CallInst *CI, AliasAnalysis *AA) { 0
595 this->CI = CI; 0
596 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction(); 0
597 ----
598 // Ignore indirect calls. ----
599 if (Callee == nullptr) 0
600 return false; 0
601 ----
602 BasicBlock *BB = CI->getParent(); 0
603 LLVMContext &Context = CI->getParent()->getContext(); 0
604 IRBuilder<> B(Context); 0
605 ----
606 // Set the builder to the instruction after the call. ----
607 B.SetInsertPoint(BB, CI->getIterator()); 0
608 ----
609 // Copy fast flags from the original call. ----
610 if (const FPMathOperator *FPOp = dyn_cast(CI)) 0
611 B.setFastMathFlags(FPOp->getFastMathFlags()); 0
612 ----
613 switch (Callee->getIntrinsicID()) { 0
614 default: 0
615 break; 0
616 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_wavefrontsize: 0
617 return !EnablePreLink && fold_wavefrontsize(CI, B); 0
618 } ----
619 ----
620 FuncInfo FInfo; 0
621 if (!parseFunctionName(Callee->getName(), FInfo)) 0
622 return false; 0
623 ----
624 // Further check the number of arguments to see if they match. ----
625 if (CI->arg_size() != FInfo.getNumArgs()) 0
626 return false; 0
627 ----
628 if (TDOFold(CI, FInfo)) 0
629 return true; 0
630 ----
631 // Under unsafe-math, evaluate calls if possible. ----
632 // According to Brian Sumner, we can do this for all f32 function calls ----
633 // using host's double function calls. ----
634 if (isUnsafeMath(CI) && evaluateCall(CI, FInfo)) 0
635 return true; 0
636 ----
637 // Specialized optimizations for each function call ----
638 switch (FInfo.getId()) { 0
639 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_RECIP: 0
640 // skip vector function ----
641 assert ((FInfo.getPrefix() == AMDGPULibFunc::NATIVE || 0
642 FInfo.getPrefix() == AMDGPULibFunc::HALF) && ----
643 "recip must be an either native or half function"); ----
644 return (getVecSize(FInfo) != 1) ? false : fold_recip(CI, B, FInfo); 0
645 ----
646 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_DIVIDE: 0
647 // skip vector function ----
648 assert ((FInfo.getPrefix() == AMDGPULibFunc::NATIVE || 0
649 FInfo.getPrefix() == AMDGPULibFunc::HALF) && ----
650 "divide must be an either native or half function"); ----
651 return (getVecSize(FInfo) != 1) ? false : fold_divide(CI, B, FInfo); 0
652 ----
653 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_POW: 0
654 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_POWR: ----
655 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_POWN: ----
656 return fold_pow(CI, B, FInfo); 0
657 ----
658 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_ROOTN: 0
659 // skip vector function ----
660 return (getVecSize(FInfo) != 1) ? false : fold_rootn(CI, B, FInfo); 0
661 ----
662 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_FMA: 0
663 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_MAD: ----
664 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_NFMA: ----
665 // skip vector function ----
666 return (getVecSize(FInfo) != 1) ? false : fold_fma_mad(CI, B, FInfo); 0
667 ----
668 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_SQRT: 0
669 return isUnsafeMath(CI) && fold_sqrt(CI, B, FInfo); 0
670 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_COS: 0
671 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_SIN: ----
672 if ((getArgType(FInfo) == AMDGPULibFunc::F32 || 0
673 getArgType(FInfo) == AMDGPULibFunc::F64) 0
674 && (FInfo.getPrefix() == AMDGPULibFunc::NOPFX)) 0
675 return fold_sincos(CI, B, AA); 0
676 ----
677 break; 0
678 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_READ_PIPE_2: 0
679 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_READ_PIPE_4: ----
680 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_WRITE_PIPE_2: ----
681 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_WRITE_PIPE_4: ----
682 return fold_read_write_pipe(CI, B, FInfo); 0
683 ----
684 default: 0
685 break; 0
686 } ----
687 ----
688 return false; 0
689 } 0
690 ----
691 bool AMDGPULibCalls::TDOFold(CallInst *CI, const FuncInfo &FInfo) { 0
692 // Table-Driven optimization ----
693 const TableRef tr = getOptTable(FInfo.getId()); 0
694 if (tr.empty()) 0
695 return false; 0
696 ----
697 int const sz = (int)tr.size(); 0
698 Value *opr0 = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
699 ----
700 if (getVecSize(FInfo) > 1) { 0
701 if (ConstantDataVector *CV = dyn_cast(opr0)) { 0
702 SmallVector DVal; 0
703 for (int eltNo = 0; eltNo < getVecSize(FInfo); ++eltNo) { 0
704 ConstantFP *eltval = dyn_cast( 0
705 CV->getElementAsConstant((unsigned)eltNo)); ----
706 assert(eltval && "Non-FP arguments in math function!"); 0
707 bool found = false; 0
708 for (int i=0; i < sz; ++i) { 0
709 if (eltval->isExactlyValue(tr[i].input)) { 0
710 DVal.push_back(tr[i].result); 0
711 found = true; 0
712 break; 0
713 } ----
714 } ----
715 if (!found) { 0
716 // This vector constants not handled yet. ----
717 return false; 0
718 } ----
719 } ----
720 LLVMContext &context = CI->getParent()->getParent()->getContext(); 0
721 Constant *nval; ----
722 if (getArgType(FInfo) == AMDGPULibFunc::F32) { 0
723 SmallVector FVal; 0
724 for (unsigned i = 0; i < DVal.size(); ++i) { 0
725 FVal.push_back((float)DVal[i]); 0
726 } ----
727 ArrayRef tmp(FVal); 0
728 nval = ConstantDataVector::get(context, tmp); 0
729 } else { // F64 0
730 ArrayRef tmp(DVal); 0
731 nval = ConstantDataVector::get(context, tmp); 0
732 } ----
733 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "AMDIC: " << *CI << " ---> " << *nval << "\n"); 0
734 replaceCall(nval); 0
735 return true; 0
736 } 0
737 } else { ----
738 // Scalar version ----
739 if (ConstantFP *CF = dyn_cast(opr0)) { 0
740 for (int i = 0; i < sz; ++i) { 0
741 if (CF->isExactlyValue(tr[i].input)) { 0
742 Value *nval = ConstantFP::get(CF->getType(), tr[i].result); 0
743 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "AMDIC: " << *CI << " ---> " << *nval << "\n"); 0
744 replaceCall(nval); 0
745 return true; 0
746 } ----
747 } ----
748 } ----
749 } ----
750 ----
751 return false; 0
752 } ----
753 ----
754 // [native_]half_recip(c) ==> 1.0/c ----
755 bool AMDGPULibCalls::fold_recip(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B, 0
756 const FuncInfo &FInfo) { ----
757 Value *opr0 = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
758 if (ConstantFP *CF = dyn_cast(opr0)) { 0
759 // Just create a normal div. Later, InstCombine will be able ----
760 // to compute the divide into a constant (avoid check float infinity ----
761 // or subnormal at this point). ----
762 Value *nval = B.CreateFDiv(ConstantFP::get(CF->getType(), 1.0), 0
763 opr0, ----
764 "recip2div"); ----
765 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "AMDIC: " << *CI << " ---> " << *nval << "\n"); 0
766 replaceCall(nval); 0
767 return true; 0
768 } ----
769 return false; 0
770 } ----
771 ----
772 // [native_]half_divide(x, c) ==> x/c ----
773 bool AMDGPULibCalls::fold_divide(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B, 0
774 const FuncInfo &FInfo) { ----
775 Value *opr0 = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
776 Value *opr1 = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
777 ConstantFP *CF0 = dyn_cast(opr0); 0
778 ConstantFP *CF1 = dyn_cast(opr1); 0
779 ----
780 if ((CF0 && CF1) || // both are constants 0
781 (CF1 && (getArgType(FInfo) == AMDGPULibFunc::F32))) 0
782 // CF1 is constant && f32 divide ----
783 { ----
784 Value *nval1 = B.CreateFDiv(ConstantFP::get(opr1->getType(), 1.0), 0
785 opr1, "__div2recip"); ----
786 Value *nval = B.CreateFMul(opr0, nval1, "__div2mul"); 0
787 replaceCall(nval); 0
788 return true; 0
789 } ----
790 return false; 0
791 } ----
792 ----
793 namespace llvm { ----
794 static double log2(double V) { 0
795 #if _XOPEN_SOURCE >= 600 || defined(_ISOC99_SOURCE) || _POSIX_C_SOURCE >= 200112L ----
796 return ::log2(V); 0
797 #else ----
798 return log(V) / numbers::ln2; ----
799 #endif ----
800 } ----
801 } ----
802 ----
803 bool AMDGPULibCalls::fold_pow(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B, 0
804 const FuncInfo &FInfo) { ----
805 assert((FInfo.getId() == AMDGPULibFunc::EI_POW || 0
806 FInfo.getId() == AMDGPULibFunc::EI_POWR || ----
807 FInfo.getId() == AMDGPULibFunc::EI_POWN) && ----
808 "fold_pow: encounter a wrong function call"); ----
809 ----
810 Value *opr0, *opr1; ----
811 ConstantFP *CF; ----
812 ConstantInt *CINT; ----
813 ConstantAggregateZero *CZero; ----
814 Type *eltType; ----
815 ----
816 opr0 = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
817 opr1 = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
818 CZero = dyn_cast(opr1); 0
819 if (getVecSize(FInfo) == 1) { 0
820 eltType = opr0->getType(); 0
821 CF = dyn_cast(opr1); 0
822 CINT = dyn_cast(opr1); 0
823 } else { ----
824 VectorType *VTy = dyn_cast(opr0->getType()); 0
825 assert(VTy && "Oprand of vector function should be of vectortype"); 0
826 eltType = VTy->getElementType(); 0
827 ConstantDataVector *CDV = dyn_cast(opr1); 0
828 ----
829 // Now, only Handle vector const whose elements have the same value. ----
830 CF = CDV ? dyn_cast_or_null(CDV->getSplatValue()) : nullptr; 0
831 CINT = CDV ? dyn_cast_or_null(CDV->getSplatValue()) : nullptr; 0
832 } ----
833 ----
834 // No unsafe math , no constant argument, do nothing ----
835 if (!isUnsafeMath(CI) && !CF && !CINT && !CZero) 0
836 return false; 0
837 ----
838 // 0x1111111 means that we don't do anything for this call. ----
839 int ci_opr1 = (CINT ? (int)CINT->getSExtValue() : 0x1111111); 0
840 ----
841 if ((CF && CF->isZero()) || (CINT && ci_opr1 == 0) || CZero) { 0
842 // pow/powr/pown(x, 0) == 1 ----
843 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "AMDIC: " << *CI << " ---> 1\n"); 0
844 Constant *cnval = ConstantFP::get(eltType, 1.0); 0
845 if (getVecSize(FInfo) > 1) { 0
846 cnval = ConstantDataVector::getSplat(getVecSize(FInfo), cnval); 0
847 } ----
848 replaceCall(cnval); 0
849 return true; 0
850 } ----
851 if ((CF && CF->isExactlyValue(1.0)) || (CINT && ci_opr1 == 1)) { 0
852 // pow/powr/pown(x, 1.0) = x ----
853 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "AMDIC: " << *CI << " ---> " << *opr0 << "\n"); 0
854 replaceCall(opr0); 0
855 return true; 0
856 } ----
857 if ((CF && CF->isExactlyValue(2.0)) || (CINT && ci_opr1 == 2)) { 0
858 // pow/powr/pown(x, 2.0) = x*x ----
859 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "AMDIC: " << *CI << " ---> " << *opr0 << " * " << *opr0 0
860 << "\n"); ----
861 Value *nval = B.CreateFMul(opr0, opr0, "__pow2"); 0
862 replaceCall(nval); 0
863 return true; 0
864 } ----
865 if ((CF && CF->isExactlyValue(-1.0)) || (CINT && ci_opr1 == -1)) { 0
866 // pow/powr/pown(x, -1.0) = 1.0/x ----
867 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "AMDIC: " << *CI << " ---> 1 / " << *opr0 << "\n"); 0
868 Constant *cnval = ConstantFP::get(eltType, 1.0); 0
869 if (getVecSize(FInfo) > 1) { 0
870 cnval = ConstantDataVector::getSplat(getVecSize(FInfo), cnval); 0
871 } ----
872 Value *nval = B.CreateFDiv(cnval, opr0, "__powrecip"); 0
873 replaceCall(nval); 0
874 return true; 0
875 } ----
876 ----
877 Module *M = CI->getModule(); 0
878 if (CF && (CF->isExactlyValue(0.5) || CF->isExactlyValue(-0.5))) { 0
879 // pow[r](x, [-]0.5) = sqrt(x) ----
880 bool issqrt = CF->isExactlyValue(0.5); 0
881 if (FunctionCallee FPExpr = 0
882 getFunction(M, AMDGPULibFunc(issqrt ? AMDGPULibFunc::EI_SQRT 0
883 : AMDGPULibFunc::EI_RSQRT, ----
884 FInfo))) { 0
885 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "AMDIC: " << *CI << " ---> " 0
886 << FInfo.getName().c_str() << "(" << *opr0 << ")\n"); ----
887 Value *nval = CreateCallEx(B,FPExpr, opr0, issqrt ? "__pow2sqrt" 0
888 : "__pow2rsqrt"); ----
889 replaceCall(nval); 0
890 return true; 0
891 } ----
892 } ----
893 ----
894 if (!isUnsafeMath(CI)) 0
895 return false; 0
896 ----
897 // Unsafe Math optimization ----
898 ----
899 // Remember that ci_opr1 is set if opr1 is integral ----
900 if (CF) { 0
901 double dval = (getArgType(FInfo) == AMDGPULibFunc::F32) 0
902 ? (double)CF->getValueAPF().convertToFloat() 0
903 : CF->getValueAPF().convertToDouble(); 0
904 int ival = (int)dval; 0
905 if ((double)ival == dval) { 0
906 ci_opr1 = ival; 0
907 } else ----
908 ci_opr1 = 0x11111111; 0
909 } ----
910 ----
911 // pow/powr/pown(x, c) = [1/](x*x*..x); where ----
912 // trunc(c) == c && the number of x == c && |c| <= 12 ----
913 unsigned abs_opr1 = (ci_opr1 < 0) ? -ci_opr1 : ci_opr1; 0
914 if (abs_opr1 <= 12) { 0
915 Constant *cnval; ----
916 Value *nval; ----
917 if (abs_opr1 == 0) { 0
918 cnval = ConstantFP::get(eltType, 1.0); 0
919 if (getVecSize(FInfo) > 1) { 0
920 cnval = ConstantDataVector::getSplat(getVecSize(FInfo), cnval); 0
921 } ----
922 nval = cnval; 0
923 } else { ----
924 Value *valx2 = nullptr; 0
925 nval = nullptr; 0
926 while (abs_opr1 > 0) { 0
927 valx2 = valx2 ? B.CreateFMul(valx2, valx2, "__powx2") : opr0; 0
928 if (abs_opr1 & 1) { 0
929 nval = nval ? B.CreateFMul(nval, valx2, "__powprod") : valx2; 0
930 } ----
931 abs_opr1 >>= 1; 0
932 } ----
933 } ----
934 ----
935 if (ci_opr1 < 0) { 0
936 cnval = ConstantFP::get(eltType, 1.0); 0
937 if (getVecSize(FInfo) > 1) { 0
938 cnval = ConstantDataVector::getSplat(getVecSize(FInfo), cnval); 0
939 } ----
940 nval = B.CreateFDiv(cnval, nval, "__1powprod"); 0
941 } ----
942 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "AMDIC: " << *CI << " ---> " 0
943 << ((ci_opr1 < 0) ? "1/prod(" : "prod(") << *opr0 ----
944 << ")\n"); ----
945 replaceCall(nval); 0
946 return true; 0
947 } ----
948 ----
949 // powr ---> exp2(y * log2(x)) ----
950 // pown/pow ---> powr(fabs(x), y) | (x & ((int)y << 31)) ----
951 FunctionCallee ExpExpr = ----
952 getFunction(M, AMDGPULibFunc(AMDGPULibFunc::EI_EXP2, FInfo)); 0
953 if (!ExpExpr) 0
954 return false; 0
955 ----
956 bool needlog = false; 0
957 bool needabs = false; 0
958 bool needcopysign = false; 0
959 Constant *cnval = nullptr; 0
960 if (getVecSize(FInfo) == 1) { 0
961 CF = dyn_cast(opr0); 0
962 ----
963 if (CF) { 0
964 double V = (getArgType(FInfo) == AMDGPULibFunc::F32) 0
965 ? (double)CF->getValueAPF().convertToFloat() 0
966 : CF->getValueAPF().convertToDouble(); 0
967 ----
968 V = log2(std::abs(V)); 0
969 cnval = ConstantFP::get(eltType, V); 0
970 needcopysign = (FInfo.getId() != AMDGPULibFunc::EI_POWR) && 0
971 CF->isNegative(); 0
972 } else { ----
973 needlog = true; 0
974 needcopysign = needabs = FInfo.getId() != AMDGPULibFunc::EI_POWR && 0
975 (!CF || CF->isNegative()); 0
976 } ----
977 } else { ----
978 ConstantDataVector *CDV = dyn_cast(opr0); 0
979 ----
980 if (!CDV) { 0
981 needlog = true; 0
982 needcopysign = needabs = FInfo.getId() != AMDGPULibFunc::EI_POWR; 0
983 } else { ----
984 assert ((int)CDV->getNumElements() == getVecSize(FInfo) && 0
985 "Wrong vector size detected"); ----
986 ----
987 SmallVector DVal; 0
988 for (int i=0; i < getVecSize(FInfo); ++i) { 0
989 double V = (getArgType(FInfo) == AMDGPULibFunc::F32) 0
990 ? (double)CDV->getElementAsFloat(i) 0
991 : CDV->getElementAsDouble(i); 0
992 if (V < 0.0) needcopysign = true; 0
993 V = log2(std::abs(V)); 0
994 DVal.push_back(V); 0
995 } ----
996 if (getArgType(FInfo) == AMDGPULibFunc::F32) { 0
997 SmallVector FVal; 0
998 for (unsigned i=0; i < DVal.size(); ++i) { 0
999 FVal.push_back((float)DVal[i]); 0
1000 } ----
1001 ArrayRef tmp(FVal); 0
1002 cnval = ConstantDataVector::get(M->getContext(), tmp); 0
1003 } else { 0
1004 ArrayRef tmp(DVal); 0
1005 cnval = ConstantDataVector::get(M->getContext(), tmp); 0
1006 } ----
1007 } 0
1008 } ----
1009 ----
1010 if (needcopysign && (FInfo.getId() == AMDGPULibFunc::EI_POW)) { 0
1011 // We cannot handle corner cases for a general pow() function, give up ----
1012 // unless y is a constant integral value. Then proceed as if it were pown. ----
1013 if (getVecSize(FInfo) == 1) { 0
1014 if (const ConstantFP *CF = dyn_cast(opr1)) { 0
1015 double y = (getArgType(FInfo) == AMDGPULibFunc::F32) 0
1016 ? (double)CF->getValueAPF().convertToFloat() 0
1017 : CF->getValueAPF().convertToDouble(); 0
1018 if (y != (double)(int64_t)y) 0
1019 return false; 0
1020 } else ----
1021 return false; 0
1022 } else { ----
1023 if (const ConstantDataVector *CDV = dyn_cast(opr1)) { 0
1024 for (int i=0; i < getVecSize(FInfo); ++i) { 0
1025 double y = (getArgType(FInfo) == AMDGPULibFunc::F32) 0
1026 ? (double)CDV->getElementAsFloat(i) 0
1027 : CDV->getElementAsDouble(i); 0
1028 if (y != (double)(int64_t)y) 0
1029 return false; 0
1030 } ----
1031 } else ----
1032 return false; 0
1033 } ----
1034 } ----
1035 ----
1036 Value *nval; ----
1037 if (needabs) { 0
1038 FunctionCallee AbsExpr = ----
1039 getFunction(M, AMDGPULibFunc(AMDGPULibFunc::EI_FABS, FInfo)); 0
1040 if (!AbsExpr) 0
1041 return false; 0
1042 nval = CreateCallEx(B, AbsExpr, opr0, "__fabs"); 0
1043 } else { ----
1044 nval = cnval ? cnval : opr0; 0
1045 } ----
1046 if (needlog) { 0
1047 FunctionCallee LogExpr = ----
1048 getFunction(M, AMDGPULibFunc(AMDGPULibFunc::EI_LOG2, FInfo)); 0
1049 if (!LogExpr) 0
1050 return false; 0
1051 nval = CreateCallEx(B,LogExpr, nval, "__log2"); 0
1052 } ----
1053 ----
1054 if (FInfo.getId() == AMDGPULibFunc::EI_POWN) { 0
1055 // convert int(32) to fp(f32 or f64) ----
1056 opr1 = B.CreateSIToFP(opr1, nval->getType(), "pownI2F"); 0
1057 } ----
1058 nval = B.CreateFMul(opr1, nval, "__ylogx"); 0
1059 nval = CreateCallEx(B,ExpExpr, nval, "__exp2"); 0
1060 ----
1061 if (needcopysign) { 0
1062 Value *opr_n; ----
1063 Type* rTy = opr0->getType(); 0
1064 Type* nTyS = eltType->isDoubleTy() ? B.getInt64Ty() : B.getInt32Ty(); 0
1065 Type *nTy = nTyS; 0
1066 if (const auto *vTy = dyn_cast(rTy)) 0
1067 nTy = FixedVectorType::get(nTyS, vTy); 0
1068 unsigned size = nTy->getScalarSizeInBits(); 0
1069 opr_n = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
1070 if (opr_n->getType()->isIntegerTy()) 0
1071 opr_n = B.CreateZExtOrBitCast(opr_n, nTy, "__ytou"); 0
1072 else ----
1073 opr_n = B.CreateFPToSI(opr1, nTy, "__ytou"); 0
1074 ----
1075 Value *sign = B.CreateShl(opr_n, size-1, "__yeven"); 0
1076 sign = B.CreateAnd(B.CreateBitCast(opr0, nTy), sign, "__pow_sign"); 0
1077 nval = B.CreateOr(B.CreateBitCast(nval, nTy), sign); 0
1078 nval = B.CreateBitCast(nval, opr0->getType()); 0
1079 } ----
1080 ----
1081 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "AMDIC: " << *CI << " ---> " 0
1082 << "exp2(" << *opr1 << " * log2(" << *opr0 << "))\n"); ----
1083 replaceCall(nval); 0
1084 ----
1085 return true; 0
1086 } ----
1087 ----
1088 bool AMDGPULibCalls::fold_rootn(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B, 0
1089 const FuncInfo &FInfo) { ----
1090 Value *opr0 = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
1091 Value *opr1 = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
1092 ----
1093 ConstantInt *CINT = dyn_cast(opr1); 0
1094 if (!CINT) { 0
1095 return false; 0
1096 } ----
1097 int ci_opr1 = (int)CINT->getSExtValue(); 0
1098 if (ci_opr1 == 1) { // rootn(x, 1) = x 0
1099 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "AMDIC: " << *CI << " ---> " << *opr0 << "\n"); 0
1100 replaceCall(opr0); 0
1101 return true; 0
1102 } ----
1103 if (ci_opr1 == 2) { // rootn(x, 2) = sqrt(x) 0
1104 Module *M = CI->getModule(); 0
1105 if (FunctionCallee FPExpr = 0
1106 getFunction(M, AMDGPULibFunc(AMDGPULibFunc::EI_SQRT, FInfo))) { 0
1107 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "AMDIC: " << *CI << " ---> sqrt(" << *opr0 << ")\n"); 0
1108 Value *nval = CreateCallEx(B,FPExpr, opr0, "__rootn2sqrt"); 0
1109 replaceCall(nval); 0
1110 return true; 0
1111 } ----
1112 } else if (ci_opr1 == 3) { // rootn(x, 3) = cbrt(x) 0
1113 Module *M = CI->getModule(); 0
1114 if (FunctionCallee FPExpr = 0
1115 getFunction(M, AMDGPULibFunc(AMDGPULibFunc::EI_CBRT, FInfo))) { 0
1116 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "AMDIC: " << *CI << " ---> cbrt(" << *opr0 << ")\n"); 0
1117 Value *nval = CreateCallEx(B,FPExpr, opr0, "__rootn2cbrt"); 0
1118 replaceCall(nval); 0
1119 return true; 0
1120 } ----
1121 } else if (ci_opr1 == -1) { // rootn(x, -1) = 1.0/x 0
1122 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "AMDIC: " << *CI << " ---> 1.0 / " << *opr0 << "\n"); 0
1123 Value *nval = B.CreateFDiv(ConstantFP::get(opr0->getType(), 1.0), 0
1124 opr0, ----
1125 "__rootn2div"); ----
1126 replaceCall(nval); 0
1127 return true; 0
1128 } else if (ci_opr1 == -2) { // rootn(x, -2) = rsqrt(x) 0
1129 Module *M = CI->getModule(); 0
1130 if (FunctionCallee FPExpr = 0
1131 getFunction(M, AMDGPULibFunc(AMDGPULibFunc::EI_RSQRT, FInfo))) { 0
1132 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "AMDIC: " << *CI << " ---> rsqrt(" << *opr0 0
1133 << ")\n"); ----
1134 Value *nval = CreateCallEx(B,FPExpr, opr0, "__rootn2rsqrt"); 0
1135 replaceCall(nval); 0
1136 return true; 0
1137 } ----
1138 } ----
1139 return false; 0
1140 } ----
1141 ----
1142 bool AMDGPULibCalls::fold_fma_mad(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B, 0
1143 const FuncInfo &FInfo) { ----
1144 Value *opr0 = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
1145 Value *opr1 = CI->getArgOperand(1); 0
1146 Value *opr2 = CI->getArgOperand(2); 0
1147 ----
1148 ConstantFP *CF0 = dyn_cast(opr0); 0
1149 ConstantFP *CF1 = dyn_cast(opr1); 0
1150 if ((CF0 && CF0->isZero()) || (CF1 && CF1->isZero())) { 0
1151 // fma/mad(a, b, c) = c if a=0 || b=0 ----
1152 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "AMDIC: " << *CI << " ---> " << *opr2 << "\n"); 0
1153 replaceCall(opr2); 0
1154 return true; 0
1155 } ----
1156 if (CF0 && CF0->isExactlyValue(1.0f)) { 0
1157 // fma/mad(a, b, c) = b+c if a=1 ----
1158 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "AMDIC: " << *CI << " ---> " << *opr1 << " + " << *opr2 0
1159 << "\n"); ----
1160 Value *nval = B.CreateFAdd(opr1, opr2, "fmaadd"); 0
1161 replaceCall(nval); 0
1162 return true; 0
1163 } ----
1164 if (CF1 && CF1->isExactlyValue(1.0f)) { 0
1165 // fma/mad(a, b, c) = a+c if b=1 ----
1166 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "AMDIC: " << *CI << " ---> " << *opr0 << " + " << *opr2 0
1167 << "\n"); ----
1168 Value *nval = B.CreateFAdd(opr0, opr2, "fmaadd"); 0
1169 replaceCall(nval); 0
1170 return true; 0
1171 } ----
1172 if (ConstantFP *CF = dyn_cast(opr2)) { 0
1173 if (CF->isZero()) { 0
1174 // fma/mad(a, b, c) = a*b if c=0 ----
1175 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "AMDIC: " << *CI << " ---> " << *opr0 << " * " 0
1176 << *opr1 << "\n"); ----
1177 Value *nval = B.CreateFMul(opr0, opr1, "fmamul"); 0
1178 replaceCall(nval); 0
1179 return true; 0
1180 } ----
1181 } ----
1182 ----
1183 return false; 0
1184 } ----
1185 ----
1186 // Get a scalar native builtin single argument FP function ----
1187 FunctionCallee AMDGPULibCalls::getNativeFunction(Module *M, 0
1188 const FuncInfo &FInfo) { ----
1189 if (getArgType(FInfo) == AMDGPULibFunc::F64 || !HasNative(FInfo.getId())) 0
1190 return nullptr; 0
1191 FuncInfo nf = FInfo; 0
1192 nf.setPrefix(AMDGPULibFunc::NATIVE); 0
1193 return getFunction(M, nf); 0
1194 } 0
1195 ----
1196 // fold sqrt -> native_sqrt (x) ----
1197 bool AMDGPULibCalls::fold_sqrt(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B, 0
1198 const FuncInfo &FInfo) { ----
1199 if (getArgType(FInfo) == AMDGPULibFunc::F32 && (getVecSize(FInfo) == 1) && 0
1200 (FInfo.getPrefix() != AMDGPULibFunc::NATIVE)) { 0
1201 if (FunctionCallee FPExpr = getNativeFunction( 0
1202 CI->getModule(), AMDGPULibFunc(AMDGPULibFunc::EI_SQRT, FInfo))) { 0
1203 Value *opr0 = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
1204 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "AMDIC: " << *CI << " ---> " 0
1205 << "sqrt(" << *opr0 << ")\n"); ----
1206 Value *nval = CreateCallEx(B,FPExpr, opr0, "__sqrt"); 0
1207 replaceCall(nval); 0
1208 return true; 0
1209 } ----
1210 } ----
1211 return false; 0
1212 } ----
1213 ----
1214 // fold sin, cos -> sincos. ----
1215 bool AMDGPULibCalls::fold_sincos(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B, 0
1216 AliasAnalysis *AA) { ----
1217 AMDGPULibFunc fInfo; 0
1218 if (!AMDGPULibFunc::parse(CI->getCalledFunction()->getName(), fInfo)) 0
1219 return false; 0
1220 ----
1221 assert(fInfo.getId() == AMDGPULibFunc::EI_SIN || 0
1222 fInfo.getId() == AMDGPULibFunc::EI_COS); ----
1223 bool const isSin = fInfo.getId() == AMDGPULibFunc::EI_SIN; 0
1224 ----
1225 Value *CArgVal = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
1226 BasicBlock * const CBB = CI->getParent(); 0
1227 ----
1228 int const MaxScan = 30; 0
1229 bool Changed = false; 0
1230 ----
1231 { // fold in load value. ----
1232 LoadInst *LI = dyn_cast(CArgVal); 0
1233 if (LI && LI->getParent() == CBB) { 0
1234 BasicBlock::iterator BBI = LI->getIterator(); 0
1235 Value *AvailableVal = FindAvailableLoadedValue(LI, CBB, BBI, MaxScan, AA); 0
1236 if (AvailableVal) { 0
1237 Changed = true; 0
1238 CArgVal->replaceAllUsesWith(AvailableVal); 0
1239 if (CArgVal->getNumUses() == 0) 0
1240 LI->eraseFromParent(); 0
1241 CArgVal = CI->getArgOperand(0); 0
1242 } ----
1243 } ----
1244 } ----
1245 ----
1246 Module *M = CI->getModule(); 0
1247 fInfo.setId(isSin ? AMDGPULibFunc::EI_COS : AMDGPULibFunc::EI_SIN); 0
1248 std::string const PairName = fInfo.mangle(); 0
1249 ----
1250 CallInst *UI = nullptr; 0
1251 for (User* U : CArgVal->users()) { 0
1252 CallInst *XI = dyn_cast_or_null(U); 0
1253 if (!XI || XI == CI || XI->getParent() != CBB) 0
1254 continue; 0
1255 ----
1256 Function *UCallee = XI->getCalledFunction(); 0
1257 if (!UCallee || !UCallee->getName().equals(PairName)) 0
1258 continue; 0
1259 ----
1260 BasicBlock::iterator BBI = CI->getIterator(); 0
1261 if (BBI == CI->getParent()->begin()) 0
1262 break; 0
1263 --BBI; 0
1264 for (int I = MaxScan; I > 0 && BBI != CBB->begin(); --BBI, --I) { 0
1265 if (cast(BBI) == XI) { 0
1266 UI = XI; 0
1267 break; 0
1268 } ----
1269 } ----
1270 if (UI) break; 0
1271 } ----
1272 ----
1273 if (!UI) 0
1274 return Changed; 0
1275 ----
1276 // Merge the sin and cos. ----
1277 ----
1278 // for OpenCL 2.0 we have only generic implementation of sincos ----
1279 // function. ----
1280 AMDGPULibFunc nf(AMDGPULibFunc::EI_SINCOS, fInfo); 0
1281 nf.getLeads()[0].PtrKind = AMDGPULibFunc::getEPtrKindFromAddrSpace(AMDGPUAS::FLAT_ADDRESS); 0
1282 FunctionCallee Fsincos = getFunction(M, nf); 0
1283 if (!Fsincos) 0
1284 return Changed; 0
1285 ----
1286 BasicBlock::iterator ItOld = B.GetInsertPoint(); 0
1287 AllocaInst *Alloc = insertAlloca(UI, B, "__sincos_"); 0
1288 B.SetInsertPoint(UI); 0
1289 ----
1290 Value *P = Alloc; 0
1291 Type *PTy = Fsincos.getFunctionType()->getParamType(1); 0
1292 // The allocaInst allocates the memory in private address space. This need ----
1293 // to be bitcasted to point to the address space of cos pointer type. ----
1294 // In OpenCL 2.0 this is generic, while in 1.2 that is private. ----
1295 if (PTy->getPointerAddressSpace() != AMDGPUAS::PRIVATE_ADDRESS) 0
1296 P = B.CreateAddrSpaceCast(Alloc, PTy); 0
1297 CallInst *Call = CreateCallEx2(B, Fsincos, UI->getArgOperand(0), P); 0
1298 ----
1299 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "AMDIC: fold_sincos (" << *CI << ", " << *UI << ") with " 0
1300 << *Call << "\n"); ----
1301 ----
1302 if (!isSin) { // CI->cos, UI->sin 0
1303 B.SetInsertPoint(&*ItOld); 0
1304 UI->replaceAllUsesWith(&*Call); 0
1305 Instruction *Reload = B.CreateLoad(Alloc->getAllocatedType(), Alloc); 0
1306 CI->replaceAllUsesWith(Reload); 0
1307 UI->eraseFromParent(); 0
1308 CI->eraseFromParent(); 0
1309 } else { // CI->sin, UI->cos ----
1310 Instruction *Reload = B.CreateLoad(Alloc->getAllocatedType(), Alloc); 0
1311 UI->replaceAllUsesWith(Reload); 0
1312 CI->replaceAllUsesWith(Call); 0
1313 UI->eraseFromParent(); 0
1314 CI->eraseFromParent(); 0
1315 } ----
1316 return true; 0
1317 } 0
1318 ----
1319 bool AMDGPULibCalls::fold_wavefrontsize(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) { 0
1320 if (!TM) 0
1321 return false; 0
1322 ----
1323 StringRef CPU = TM->getTargetCPU(); 0
1324 StringRef Features = TM->getTargetFeatureString(); 0
1325 if ((CPU.empty() || CPU.equals_insensitive("generic")) && 0
1326 (Features.empty() || !Features.contains_insensitive("wavefrontsize"))) 0
1327 return false; 0
1328 ----
1329 Function *F = CI->getParent()->getParent(); 0
1330 const GCNSubtarget &ST = TM->getSubtarget(*F); 0
1331 unsigned N = ST.getWavefrontSize(); 0
1332 ----
1333 LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "AMDIC: fold_wavefrontsize (" << *CI << ") with " 0
1334 << N << "\n"); ----
1335 ----
1336 CI->replaceAllUsesWith(ConstantInt::get(B.getInt32Ty(), N)); 0
1337 CI->eraseFromParent(); 0
1338 return true; 0
1339 } ----
1340 ----
1341 // Get insertion point at entry. ----
1342 BasicBlock::iterator AMDGPULibCalls::getEntryIns(CallInst * UI) { 0
1343 Function * Func = UI->getParent()->getParent(); 0
1344 BasicBlock * BB = &Func->getEntryBlock(); 0
1345 assert(BB && "Entry block not found!"); 0
1346 BasicBlock::iterator ItNew = BB->begin(); 0
1347 return ItNew; 0
1348 } ----
1349 ----
1350 // Insert a AllocsInst at the beginning of function entry block. ----
1351 AllocaInst* AMDGPULibCalls::insertAlloca(CallInst *UI, IRBuilder<> &B, 0
1352 const char *prefix) { ----
1353 BasicBlock::iterator ItNew = getEntryIns(UI); 0
1354 Function *UCallee = UI->getCalledFunction(); 0
1355 Type *RetType = UCallee->getReturnType(); 0
1356 B.SetInsertPoint(&*ItNew); 0
1357 AllocaInst *Alloc = ----
1358 B.CreateAlloca(RetType, nullptr, std::string(prefix) + UI->getName()); 0
1359 Alloc->setAlignment( 0
1360 Align(UCallee->getParent()->getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(RetType))); 0
1361 return Alloc; 0
1362 } ----
1363 ----
1364 bool AMDGPULibCalls::evaluateScalarMathFunc(const FuncInfo &FInfo, 0
1365 double& Res0, double& Res1, ----
1366 Constant *copr0, Constant *copr1, ----
1367 Constant *copr2) { ----
1368 // By default, opr0/opr1/opr3 holds values of float/double type. ----
1369 // If they are not float/double, each function has to its ----
1370 // operand separately. ----
1371 double opr0=0.0, opr1=0.0, opr2=0.0; 0
1372 ConstantFP *fpopr0 = dyn_cast_or_null(copr0); 0
1373 ConstantFP *fpopr1 = dyn_cast_or_null(copr1); 0
1374 ConstantFP *fpopr2 = dyn_cast_or_null(copr2); 0
1375 if (fpopr0) { 0
1376 opr0 = (getArgType(FInfo) == AMDGPULibFunc::F64) 0
1377 ? fpopr0->getValueAPF().convertToDouble() 0
1378 : (double)fpopr0->getValueAPF().convertToFloat(); 0
1379 } ----
1380 ----
1381 if (fpopr1) { 0
1382 opr1 = (getArgType(FInfo) == AMDGPULibFunc::F64) 0
1383 ? fpopr1->getValueAPF().convertToDouble() 0
1384 : (double)fpopr1->getValueAPF().convertToFloat(); 0
1385 } ----
1386 ----
1387 if (fpopr2) { 0
1388 opr2 = (getArgType(FInfo) == AMDGPULibFunc::F64) 0
1389 ? fpopr2->getValueAPF().convertToDouble() 0
1390 : (double)fpopr2->getValueAPF().convertToFloat(); 0
1391 } ----
1392 ----
1393 switch (FInfo.getId()) { 0
1394 default : return false; 0
1395 ----
1396 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_ACOS: 0
1397 Res0 = acos(opr0); 0
1398 return true; 0
1399 ----
1400 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_ACOSH: 0
1401 // acosh(x) == log(x + sqrt(x*x - 1)) ----
1402 Res0 = log(opr0 + sqrt(opr0*opr0 - 1.0)); 0
1403 return true; 0
1404 ----
1405 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_ACOSPI: 0
1406 Res0 = acos(opr0) / MATH_PI; 0
1407 return true; 0
1408 ----
1409 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_ASIN: 0
1410 Res0 = asin(opr0); 0
1411 return true; 0
1412 ----
1413 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_ASINH: 0
1414 // asinh(x) == log(x + sqrt(x*x + 1)) ----
1415 Res0 = log(opr0 + sqrt(opr0*opr0 + 1.0)); 0
1416 return true; 0
1417 ----
1418 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_ASINPI: 0
1419 Res0 = asin(opr0) / MATH_PI; 0
1420 return true; 0
1421 ----
1422 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_ATAN: 0
1423 Res0 = atan(opr0); 0
1424 return true; 0
1425 ----
1426 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_ATANH: 0
1427 // atanh(x) == (log(x+1) - log(x-1))/2; ----
1428 Res0 = (log(opr0 + 1.0) - log(opr0 - 1.0))/2.0; 0
1429 return true; 0
1430 ----
1431 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_ATANPI: 0
1432 Res0 = atan(opr0) / MATH_PI; 0
1433 return true; 0
1434 ----
1435 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_CBRT: 0
1436 Res0 = (opr0 < 0.0) ? -pow(-opr0, 1.0/3.0) : pow(opr0, 1.0/3.0); 0
1437 return true; 0
1438 ----
1439 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_COS: 0
1440 Res0 = cos(opr0); 0
1441 return true; 0
1442 ----
1443 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_COSH: 0
1444 Res0 = cosh(opr0); 0
1445 return true; 0
1446 ----
1447 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_COSPI: 0
1448 Res0 = cos(MATH_PI * opr0); 0
1449 return true; 0
1450 ----
1451 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_EXP: 0
1452 Res0 = exp(opr0); 0
1453 return true; 0
1454 ----
1455 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_EXP2: 0
1456 Res0 = pow(2.0, opr0); 0
1457 return true; 0
1458 ----
1459 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_EXP10: 0
1460 Res0 = pow(10.0, opr0); 0
1461 return true; 0
1462 ----
1463 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_EXPM1: 0
1464 Res0 = exp(opr0) - 1.0; 0
1465 return true; 0
1466 ----
1467 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_LOG: 0
1468 Res0 = log(opr0); 0
1469 return true; 0
1470 ----
1471 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_LOG2: 0
1472 Res0 = log(opr0) / log(2.0); 0
1473 return true; 0
1474 ----
1475 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_LOG10: 0
1476 Res0 = log(opr0) / log(10.0); 0
1477 return true; 0
1478 ----
1479 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_RSQRT: 0
1480 Res0 = 1.0 / sqrt(opr0); 0
1481 return true; 0
1482 ----
1483 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_SIN: 0
1484 Res0 = sin(opr0); 0
1485 return true; 0
1486 ----
1487 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_SINH: 0
1488 Res0 = sinh(opr0); 0
1489 return true; 0
1490 ----
1491 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_SINPI: 0
1492 Res0 = sin(MATH_PI * opr0); 0
1493 return true; 0
1494 ----
1495 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_SQRT: 0
1496 Res0 = sqrt(opr0); 0
1497 return true; 0
1498 ----
1499 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_TAN: 0
1500 Res0 = tan(opr0); 0
1501 return true; 0
1502 ----
1503 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_TANH: 0
1504 Res0 = tanh(opr0); 0
1505 return true; 0
1506 ----
1507 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_TANPI: 0
1508 Res0 = tan(MATH_PI * opr0); 0
1509 return true; 0
1510 ----
1511 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_RECIP: 0
1512 Res0 = 1.0 / opr0; 0
1513 return true; 0
1514 ----
1515 // two-arg functions ----
1516 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_DIVIDE: 0
1517 Res0 = opr0 / opr1; 0
1518 return true; 0
1519 ----
1520 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_POW: 0
1521 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_POWR: ----
1522 Res0 = pow(opr0, opr1); 0
1523 return true; 0
1524 ----
1525 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_POWN: { 0
1526 if (ConstantInt *iopr1 = dyn_cast_or_null(copr1)) { 0
1527 double val = (double)iopr1->getSExtValue(); 0
1528 Res0 = pow(opr0, val); 0
1529 return true; 0
1530 } ----
1531 return false; 0
1532 } ----
1533 ----
1534 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_ROOTN: { 0
1535 if (ConstantInt *iopr1 = dyn_cast_or_null(copr1)) { 0
1536 double val = (double)iopr1->getSExtValue(); 0
1537 Res0 = pow(opr0, 1.0 / val); 0
1538 return true; 0
1539 } ----
1540 return false; 0
1541 } ----
1542 ----
1543 // with ptr arg ----
1544 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_SINCOS: 0
1545 Res0 = sin(opr0); 0
1546 Res1 = cos(opr0); 0
1547 return true; 0
1548 ----
1549 // three-arg functions ----
1550 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_FMA: 0
1551 case AMDGPULibFunc::EI_MAD: ----
1552 Res0 = opr0 * opr1 + opr2; 0
1553 return true; 0
1554 } ----
1555 ----
1556 return false; ----
1557 } ----
1558 ----
1559 bool AMDGPULibCalls::evaluateCall(CallInst *aCI, const FuncInfo &FInfo) { 0
1560 int numArgs = (int)aCI->arg_size(); 0
1561 if (numArgs > 3) 0
1562 return false; 0
1563 ----
1564 Constant *copr0 = nullptr; 0
1565 Constant *copr1 = nullptr; 0
1566 Constant *copr2 = nullptr; 0
1567 if (numArgs > 0) { 0
1568 if ((copr0 = dyn_cast(aCI->getArgOperand(0))) == nullptr) 0
1569 return false; 0
1570 } ----
1571 ----
1572 if (numArgs > 1) { 0
1573 if ((copr1 = dyn_cast(aCI->getArgOperand(1))) == nullptr) { 0
1574 if (FInfo.getId() != AMDGPULibFunc::EI_SINCOS) 0
1575 return false; 0
1576 } ----
1577 } ----
1578 ----
1579 if (numArgs > 2) { 0
1580 if ((copr2 = dyn_cast(aCI->getArgOperand(2))) == nullptr) 0
1581 return false; 0
1582 } ----
1583 ----
1584 // At this point, all arguments to aCI are constants. ----
1585 ----
1586 // max vector size is 16, and sincos will generate two results. ----
1587 double DVal0[16], DVal1[16]; ----
1588 int FuncVecSize = getVecSize(FInfo); 0
1589 bool hasTwoResults = (FInfo.getId() == AMDGPULibFunc::EI_SINCOS); 0
1590 if (FuncVecSize == 1) { 0
1591 if (!evaluateScalarMathFunc(FInfo, DVal0[0], 0
1592 DVal1[0], copr0, copr1, copr2)) { ----
1593 return false; 0
1594 } ----
1595 } else { ----
1596 ConstantDataVector *CDV0 = dyn_cast_or_null(copr0); 0
1597 ConstantDataVector *CDV1 = dyn_cast_or_null(copr1); 0
1598 ConstantDataVector *CDV2 = dyn_cast_or_null(copr2); 0
1599 for (int i = 0; i < FuncVecSize; ++i) { 0
1600 Constant *celt0 = CDV0 ? CDV0->getElementAsConstant(i) : nullptr; 0
1601 Constant *celt1 = CDV1 ? CDV1->getElementAsConstant(i) : nullptr; 0
1602 Constant *celt2 = CDV2 ? CDV2->getElementAsConstant(i) : nullptr; 0
1603 if (!evaluateScalarMathFunc(FInfo, DVal0[i], 0
1604 DVal1[i], celt0, celt1, celt2)) { 0
1605 return false; 0
1606 } ----
1607 } ----
1608 } ----
1609 ----
1610 LLVMContext &context = CI->getParent()->getParent()->getContext(); 0
1611 Constant *nval0, *nval1; ----
1612 if (FuncVecSize == 1) { 0
1613 nval0 = ConstantFP::get(CI->getType(), DVal0[0]); 0
1614 if (hasTwoResults) 0
1615 nval1 = ConstantFP::get(CI->getType(), DVal1[0]); 0
1616 } else { ----
1617 if (getArgType(FInfo) == AMDGPULibFunc::F32) { 0
1618 SmallVector FVal0, FVal1; 0
1619 for (int i = 0; i < FuncVecSize; ++i) 0
1620 FVal0.push_back((float)DVal0[i]); 0
1621 ArrayRef tmp0(FVal0); 0
1622 nval0 = ConstantDataVector::get(context, tmp0); 0
1623 if (hasTwoResults) { 0
1624 for (int i = 0; i < FuncVecSize; ++i) 0
1625 FVal1.push_back((float)DVal1[i]); 0
1626 ArrayRef tmp1(FVal1); 0
1627 nval1 = ConstantDataVector::get(context, tmp1); 0
1628 } ----
1629 } else { 0
1630 ArrayRef tmp0(DVal0); 0
1631 nval0 = ConstantDataVector::get(context, tmp0); 0
1632 if (hasTwoResults) { 0
1633 ArrayRef tmp1(DVal1); 0
1634 nval1 = ConstantDataVector::get(context, tmp1); 0
1635 } ----
1636 } ----
1637 } ----
1638 ----
1639 if (hasTwoResults) { 0
1640 // sincos ----
1641 assert(FInfo.getId() == AMDGPULibFunc::EI_SINCOS && 0
1642 "math function with ptr arg not supported yet"); ----
1643 new StoreInst(nval1, aCI->getArgOperand(1), aCI); 0
1644 } ----
1645 ----
1646 replaceCall(nval0); 0
1647 return true; 0
1648 } ----
1649 ----
1650 // Public interface to the Simplify LibCalls pass. ----
1651 FunctionPass *llvm::createAMDGPUSimplifyLibCallsPass(const TargetMachine *TM) { 0
1652 return new AMDGPUSimplifyLibCalls(TM); 0
1653 } ----
1654 ----
1655 FunctionPass *llvm::createAMDGPUUseNativeCallsPass() { 0
1656 return new AMDGPUUseNativeCalls(); 0
1657 } ----
1658 ----
1659 bool AMDGPUSimplifyLibCalls::runOnFunction(Function &F) { 0
1660 if (skipFunction(F)) 0
1661 return false; 0
1662 ----
1663 bool Changed = false; 0
1664 auto AA = &getAnalysis().getAAResults(); 0
1665 ----
1666 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "AMDIC: process function "; 0
1667 F.printAsOperand(dbgs(), false, F.getParent()); dbgs() << '\n';); ----
1668 ----
1669 for (auto &BB : F) { 0
1670 for (BasicBlock::iterator I = BB.begin(), E = BB.end(); I != E; ) { 0
1671 // Ignore non-calls. ----
1672 CallInst *CI = dyn_cast(I); 0
1673 ++I; 0
1674 // Ignore intrinsics that do not become real instructions. ----
1675 if (!CI || isa(CI) || CI->isLifetimeStartOrEnd()) 0
1676 continue; 0
1677 ----
1678 // Ignore indirect calls. ----
1679 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction(); 0
1680 if (Callee == nullptr) 0
1681 continue; 0
1682 ----
1683 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "AMDIC: try folding " << *CI << "\n"; 0
1684 dbgs().flush()); ----
1685 if(Simplifier.fold(CI, AA)) 0
1686 Changed = true; 0
1687 } ----
1688 } ----
1689 return Changed; 0
1690 } ----
1691 ----
1692 PreservedAnalyses AMDGPUSimplifyLibCallsPass::run(Function &F, 0
1693 FunctionAnalysisManager &AM) { ----
1694 AMDGPULibCalls Simplifier(&TM); 0
